ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='We have gathered a lot of information. Let\'s now systematically revi
ew the PR against the checklist.\n\n## Review Checklist\n\n### 1. 全链路完整性 (
Full-chain completeness)\n- DB: New migration `CreateUsersAndUserProfiles` added
. BUT there is a conflict: `InitialSchema` already creates `users` and `user_pro
files` with `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS`. The new migration also creates them wi
th `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS`. However, the schemas differ (e.g., `deleted_at`
vs no `deleted_at`, column types like `VARCHAR(32)` vs `VARCHAR(100)`, `avatar_u
rl` missing in old, `photo_urls` missing in old, `age_range_min/max` vs `preferr
ed_min_age/max`, `user_id` as PK in old vs `id` as PK in new). Since `IF NOT EXI
STS` is used, the second migration will be skipped if tables already exist, but 
this means the new schema is not applied. If run on a fresh DB, `InitialSchema` 
creates tables first, then `CreateUsersAndUserProfiles` is skipped. So the new m
igration is effectively dead code or worse, it creates different tables if run b
efore `InitialSchema`. This is a major issue. Also, there are duplicate entity d
efinitions: old ones in `database/entities/` and new ones in `modules/auth/entit
ies/`. The old ones are still there and referenced by `autoLoadEntities: true` i
n `app.module.ts`. This will cause TypeORM to see duplicate entities for the sam
e tables, leading to errors.\n- API: Auth controller, service, DTOs, guard, conf
ig, decorator, filter are present. Looks complete.\n- Mobile: Auth BLoC, login p
age, repository, secure storage, interceptor, DI, app.dart are present. Looks co
mplete.\n- Shared-types: `packages/shared-types/src/index.ts` updated to export 
generated auth types.\n- BUT: The old `database/entities/` files are still prese
nt and may conflict. The `InitialSchema` migration already creates the tables, s
o the new migration is redundant and conflicting.\n\n### 2. 规范符合性 (Conventi
ons)\n- NestJS分层: Controller -> Service -> Repository/Entity. The service uses
Repository directly, which is acceptable in NestJS with TypeORM. DTOs are used. 
However, `AuthService` returns `AuthResponseDto` which is good. But `generateTok
ens` returns `AuthResponseDto` with `is_new_user: false` hardcoded, then overwri
