ch builds? No, jest runs ts-jest on source). But BDD tests use `dist/`. If `make
test` doesn\'t build the API first, BDD tests will fail. The Makefile `test` tar
get runs `cd apps/api && npm test` then `cd packages/shared-types && npm test` e
tc., then `make test-bdd`. It does NOT run `npm run build` in the API before BDD
. So `bdd-setup.js` will fail because `dist/` might not exist or be stale. This 
