plemented. The PR should have updated this.\n- `docs/exec-plans/TASK-auth-login.
md` status is "执行中". Should be updated to "已完成" or similar.\n- `prd/v1-aut
h-login.md` status is "待评审". Might need update but maybe not part of this PR.
\n\n### 6. 可运行性 (Runnability)\n- We can\'t run `make test` etc. But we can i
nfer issues:\n  - Duplicate entity definitions will likely cause TypeORM to fail
at startup (`autoLoadEntities: true` scans all `.entity.ts` files). Both `databa
se/entities/user.entity.ts` and `modules/auth/entities/user.entity.ts` define `@
Entity("users")`. TypeORM will throw an error about duplicate entity definitions
.\n  - The `CreateUsersAndUserProfiles` migration has the same timestamp as `Ini
tialSchema` (`20250410000000`). Migration filenames should be unique. Having the
same timestamp is bad practice and could cause ordering issues. Actually, TypeOR
M runs migrations in alphabetical order. If they have the same timestamp, the or
der between them is undefined (depends on the description part). Since both crea
te the same tables with `IF NOT EXISTS`, it\'s messy.\n  - The `bdd-setup.js` re
quires `../../../apps/api/dist/modules/auth/auth.module`. This means the API mus
t be built before BDD tests run. `make test` runs `cd apps/api && npm test` (whi
ch builds? No, jest runs ts-jest on source). But BDD tests use `dist/`. If `make
test` doesn\'t build the API first, BDD tests will fail. The Makefile `test` tar
get runs `cd apps/api && npm test` then `cd packages/shared-types && npm test` e
tc., then `make test-bdd`. It does NOT run `npm run build` in the API before BDD
. So `bdd-setup.js` will fail because `dist/` might not exist or be stale. This 
is a potential issue. Wait, `bdd-setup.js` uses `require(\'../../../apps/api/dis
t/modules/auth/auth.module\')`. This is a hard dependency on compiled JS. If the
source changed but `dist` wasn\'t rebuilt, tests run against stale code. This is
a bug in the BDD setup.\n  - `make lint`: We need to check if there are lint iss
ues. The mobile `pubspec.yaml` adds `equatable` dependency but we saw `auth_even
t.dart` and `auth_state.dart` use `equatable`. That\'s fine.\n  - `make check-do
cs`: We should see if there are any broken links. The `docs/modules/auth.md` ref
erences `apps/api/src/common/filters/all-exceptions.filter.ts` and `current-user
.decorator.ts` which exist. Good.\n\n### Additional issues\n- `AuthBloc._onToken
Refreshed` is empty. It says "Handled by interceptor; this event can be used for
explicit refresh triggers." But if it\'s not implemented, it\'s fine for now.\n-
`AuthInterceptor._clearTokensAndRedirect` clears tokens but does not actually re
direct (no navigation logic). It just clears storage. The BLoC might not be noti
fied. However, the interceptor doesn\'t have access to BuildContext, so it can\'
t navigate. The next request after token refresh failure will likely fail and th
e BLoC might emit `AuthFailure`? Actually, the interceptor rejects the request. 
The repository throws an exception. The BLoC catches it and emits `AuthFailure`.
But the UI is supposed to react to `AuthFailure` by showing a snackbar, not redi
recting. In `app.dart`, only `AuthUnauthenticated` or `AuthFailure` triggers red
irect to `/login`. Wait, `app.dart` has:\n  ```dart\n  } else if (state is AuthU
nauthenticated || state is AuthFailure) {\n    _router.go(\'/login\');\n  }\n  `
``\n  So `AuthFailure` does trigger redirect. Good.\n- `LoginPage` uses `Scaffol
dMessenger.of(context).showSnackBar` inside `BlocListener` and also in `_onSendC
ode` and `_onLogin`. In `_onLogin`, it shows snackbar for validation errors, whi
ch is fine. But for `AuthFailure`, the `BlocListener` shows the snackbar. Howeve
r, `BlocListener` is a sibling of the column, not wrapping the scaffold. Actuall
y `BlocListener` is inside the `Scaffold` body, so `ScaffoldMessenger` is availa
