elative paths from the mobile app to the generated package's `lib/` directory. T
his is unusual but might work if the analyzer treats them as part of the same pa
ckage? Actually, importing files from another package using relative paths outsi
de the current package's `lib/` is generally not allowed by the Dart analyzer. T
he correct way is to import using package URIs: `package:social_world_auth_model
s/...`. However, the generated package's files might be organized such that `lib
/api.dart` exports everything. But the mobile code imports specific files direct
ly via relative paths crossing package boundaries. This is likely to cause analy
sis errors.\n\nWait, the path is `../../models/generated/auth/lib/model/login200
_response.dart`. The mobile app's `lib/` directory is `apps/mobile/lib/`. The ge
nerated package is at `apps/mobile/lib/models/generated/auth/`. So the relative 
